description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Community Staff Nurse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about promoting independence within our community? Coastal Community Nurses are searching for a dynamic and skilled Nurse to join our newly enhanced team as the Band 5 nurse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Health and Wellbeing Team is an integrated professional team which includes social care, occupational and physiotherapy, nursing, pharmacy and support workers to support patients within our Zone in their own homes. The team are proactive and have a forward-thinking core who promote a positive and a ‘can do’ attitude. The successful candidate will be dynamic and key in managing patients to remain in their own home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic registered nurse, preferably with some community experience to work within the Coastal Community Nursing Team. You should be committed to and have proven ability to deliver a high standard of care to patients within their own home. The successful candidate will demonstrate excellent communication skills, have the ability to manage and prioritise their own caseload, whilst working as a member of the integrated healthcare team. The applicant needs to be flexible and able to meet the challenges of working in a busy community setting. You will be joining a truly multi-disciplinary team which aims to prevent hospital admissions, facilitate safe and effective discharges home and support patients in their own homes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is for 37.5 hours to include weekend working on a rota system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
